li.p:
If
\twovec{a}{b} = \twovec{r\cos\theta}{r\sin\theta}, \twovec{c}{d} = \twovec{s\cos\phi}{s\sin\phi}\text{,}
then S\circ T has the effect of stretching a vector by rs and rotating it by \theta + \phi.

 No matter which order we multiply the matrices, we
	find that their product is

	    \left[\begin{array}{rr}
	    r\cos\theta \amp -r\sin\theta \\
	    r\sin\theta \amp r\sin\theta \\
	    \end{array}\right]\text{.}

If
\twovec{a}{b} = \twovec{r\cos\theta}{r\sin\theta}, \twovec{c}{d} = \twovec{s\cos\phi}{s\sin\phi}\text{,}
then S\circ T has the effect of stretching a vector by rs and rotating it by \theta + \phi.

We have
\begin{array}{rl}
\left[\begin{array}{rr} \cos\theta \amp -\sin\theta \\ \sin\theta \amp \cos\theta \\ \end{array}\right] \amp \left[\begin{array}{rr} 1 \amp 0 \\ 0 \amp -1 \\ \end{array}\right]
\left[\begin{array}{rr} \cos\theta \amp \sin\theta \\ -\sin\theta \amp \cos\theta \\ \end{array}\right] \\ = \amp
\left[\begin{array}{rr} \cos\theta \amp -\sin\theta \\ \sin\theta \amp \cos\theta \\ \end{array}\right]
\left[\begin{array}{rr} \cos\theta \amp \sin\theta \\ \sin\theta \amp -\cos\theta \\ \end{array}\right] \\ = \amp \left[\begin{array}{rr} \cos(2\theta) \amp \sin(2\theta) \\ \sin(2\theta) \amp -\cos(2\theta) \\ \end{array}\right] \text{.} \end{array}

We have

  \begin{array}{rl}
  \left[\begin{array}{rr}
  \cos\theta \amp -\sin\theta \\
  \sin\theta \amp \cos\theta \\
  \end{array}\right]
  \left[\begin{array}{rr}
  1 \amp 0 \\
  0 \amp -1 \\
  \end{array}\right] \amp 
  \left[\begin{array}{rr}
  \cos\theta \amp \sin\theta \\
  -\sin\theta \amp \cos\theta \\
  \end{array}\right]
  \\
  =
  \amp
  \left[\begin{array}{rr}
  \cos(2\theta) \amp \sin(2\theta) \\
  \sin(2\theta) \amp -\cos(2\theta) \\
  \end{array}\right]
  \text{.}
  \end{array}
